## Code Conventions

### Python
- Use `async/await` everywhere — this is an async-first system
- Pydantic v2 for all data models — define in `packages/shared/`
- Type hints on every function signature
- Never use `print()` — use `loguru` logger
- Errors: raise typed exceptions, catch at the route level
- Every agent function returns a typed Pydantic model

### API Design
- RESTful routes in `packages/api/routes/`
- All routes use dependency injection for auth
- Response envelope: `{ "data": ..., "meta": { "query_id": ..., "cost": ..., "blocked": bool } }`
- Every query gets a UUID — traceable end to end

### LangGraph
- Define state as a TypedDict
- Each agent is a node in the graph
- Privacy Guard is always the last node before output
- Use `conditional_edges` for routing logic

### React
- Components in `packages/web/src/components/`
- No class components — hooks only
- Tailwind for all styling — no inline styles
- Real-time updates via Supabase Realtime

---

## What Agents Must Never Do
- Return raw database rows to any external party
- Skip the Privacy Guard node
- Hardcode API keys — use environment variables always
- Write synchronous blocking code in async functions
- Create files outside the defined monorepo structure
- Use `any` type in TypeScript or skip type hints in Python

---

## Environment Variables
All secrets live in `.env` (never committed). Structure:
```
GEMINI_API_KEY=
SUPABASE_URL=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY=
SPEECHMATICS_API_KEY=
FEATHERLESS_API_KEY=
```

